<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF636ADCFA899AF117FBB60D" pageId="152" pageNumber="913" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF636ADCFA899AF117FBB60D" blockId="152.[1395,2606,2766,3470]" pageId="152" pageNumber="913">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF636ADCFA899AF118D9B7FB" bold="true" box="[1397,1753,3240,3273]" pageId="152" pageNumber="913">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Near Threatened on The IUCN Red List. The 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF636ADCFA889A961BD5B7C2" box="[1396,1493,3279,3312]" name="Taiwan" pageId="152" pageNumber="913">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
Tube-nosed Bat has a relatively restricted range. It may be affected by deforestation, although this is no longer carried outto a significant degree on the higher elevations of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF636ADCFA1A9B47184BB60D" box="[1510,1611,3358,3391]" name="Taiwan" pageId="152" pageNumber="913">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. The species has been regionally redlisted in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF636ADCF7369B47171EB60D" box="[2250,2334,3358,3391]" name="China" pageId="152" pageNumber="913">China</collectingCountry>
as endangered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
